  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Terai Floods Initial Response</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">ADRA Nepal is responding with an initial response to provide shelter kits, hygiene kits, and food rations to 950 HHs, and provide essential medicines and sanitary supplies to be distributed at the government health center</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&#x2022;	Heavy rainfalls in the Terai region of Nepal has caused flooding and landslides, leading to displacement, food scarcity, and disease
&#x2022;	According to the latest update circulated by the government (MOHA) altogether 123 people have been dead, 39 injured while 35 people have gone missing. Additionally, 18,320 families have been temporarily displaced, 7000+ houses have been destroyed and approximately, 75,000 individuals have been affected by this catastrophe.

&#x2022;	Since more than 7000 houses have been destroyed and the reserved food stock, the demands for temporary shelter and ready to eat food packages is on the rise. The survivors have been taking temporary shelter in the schools and community buildings. The flood survivors residing near the banks of the river have started to complain about a different kind of disease. The scarcity of clean water has forced the survivors to drink contaminated water and unhygienic food stocks. Hence, more cases of fever, diarrhea, skin allergies because of exposure to polluted water is on the rise.</narrative>
  </description>
